photo.title: San Francisco - Financial District: Matson Building

description._content: The Matson Building, at 215 Market Street, was built in 1923 by Bliss & Faville as the mainland headquarters for Hawaii's Big Five corporations.  After damage experienced during the 1909 Loma Prieta earthquake, the 18-story beaux arts buidling was joined along with wo annex buildings, as one during a 3-year $178 million overhaul to create the renovated PG&E Headquarters.
